00:32:33.735 --> 00:32:37.271 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In what ways did you see
the brothers and sisters

00:32:37.271 --> 00:32:40.074 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
giving all they could in the ministry?

00:32:40.074 --> 00:32:42.543 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They witnessed at every opportunity.

00:32:42.543 --> 00:32:46.080 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They preached door to door,
in public witnessing,

00:32:46.080 --> 00:32:50.551 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at businesses, informally,
and in remote areas.

00:32:50.551 --> 00:32:54.222 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They used our Teaching Toolbox,
including videos,

00:32:54.222 --> 00:32:58.926 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to reach people
in a language they really understood.

00:32:58.926 --> 00:33:01.796 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The ministry is an important way

00:33:01.796 --> 00:33:04.999 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we imitate Jehovah’s love for people.

00:33:04.999 --> 00:33:08.670 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We also want to imitate Jehovah’s holiness.

00:33:08.670 --> 00:33:13.675 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Herd explained
why we strive to stay morally clean.

00:33:13.675 --> 00:33:16.611 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But what about keeping physically clean?

00:33:16.611 --> 00:33:19.480 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s not always easy for busy Christians.

00:33:19.480 --> 00:33:21.549 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In this dramatization,

00:33:21.549 --> 00:33:23.885 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
see how Grayson gives his son

00:33:23.885 --> 00:33:27.889 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the loving counsel on cleanliness that he needs.

00:33:33.861 --> 00:33:36.197 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I graduated
from high school that summer

00:33:36.197 --> 00:33:37.765 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and wanted to start
regular pioneering.

00:33:39.100 --> 00:33:41.936 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s my dad, Grayson.

00:33:44.138 --> 00:33:46.808 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Dad was having
car trouble that morning

00:33:46.808 --> 00:33:49.444 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and needed a ride to work,
so I gave him one.

00:33:53.214 --> 00:33:57.452 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
OK, my car
was a little messy and smelly.

00:34:03.257 --> 00:34:06.894 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I mean, it was winter,
and my car is pretty old anyway.

00:34:06.894 --> 00:34:08.096 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So why bother?

00:34:08.096 --> 00:34:11.065 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When I get a new car,
then I’ll keep it clean.

00:34:12.500 --> 00:34:15.336 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But he was making
a big deal out of nothing.

00:34:20.641 --> 00:34:25.546 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That morning was not good.

00:34:33.354 --> 00:34:36.090 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I thought it was over.

00:34:36.090 --> 00:34:39.160 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But later that evening,
Dad brought it up again.

00:34:40.261 --> 00:34:42.797 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But this time, it went better.

00:34:44.499 --> 00:34:47.335 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He showed me a picture of his first car.

00:34:47.335 --> 00:34:49.370 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It looked pretty old too.

00:34:49.370 --> 00:34:52.173 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He said that while our home
or car may not be

00:34:52.173 --> 00:34:56.144 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
fancy or luxurious,
it should be as clean and presentable

00:34:56.144 --> 00:34:57.912 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
as circumstances allow.

00:34:59.514 --> 00:35:02.150 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I still didn’t see what the big deal was.

00:35:02.150 --> 00:35:05.353 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then, he explained
that Jehovah is a clean God,

00:35:05.353 --> 00:35:07.789 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and from ancient times,
he has always required

00:35:07.789 --> 00:35:09.957 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that his people be a clean people.

00:35:11.092 --> 00:35:13.194 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Under the Mosaic Law
that Jehovah gave to Israel,

00:35:14.061 --> 00:35:17.231 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
cleanness and worship
were inseparable.

00:35:19.033 --> 00:35:21.035 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It specified that priests were required

00:35:21.035 --> 00:35:23.037 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to wash their hands and feet

00:35:23.037 --> 00:35:25.339 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
before offering sacrifices to Jehovah.

00:35:25.339 --> 00:35:28.042 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
While in an unclean state, an Israelite

00:35:28.042 --> 00:35:30.878 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
could not have any part in worship,

00:35:30.878 --> 00:35:33.748 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or it could mean death.

00:35:36.884 --> 00:35:39.587 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I said, “I’m not an Israelite,

00:35:39.587 --> 00:35:41.756 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and we’re not
under the Mosaic Law anymore.”

00:35:42.890 --> 00:35:45.259 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He said, “True, but it gives us insight

00:35:45.259 --> 00:35:47.361 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
into Jehovah’s thinking.”

00:35:47.361 --> 00:35:48.896 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Law emphasized that cleanness

00:35:48.896 --> 00:35:52.200 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was required
of all those who worshipped him.

00:35:52.200 --> 00:35:55.102 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And as Malachi 3:6 tells us,

00:35:55.102 --> 00:35:57.271 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Jehovah has not changed.’

00:35:59.240 --> 00:36:02.176 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then, he said something
that really stuck with me,

00:36:03.244 --> 00:36:06.180 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Besides, it’s not all about us.”

00:36:07.048 --> 00:36:09.784 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then, he gave me a scripture to look up.

00:36:10.418 --> 00:36:13.988 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was 2 Corinthians 6:3, 4:

00:36:14.622 --> 00:36:18.626 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“In no way are we giving
any cause for stumbling,

00:36:18.626 --> 00:36:22.096 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“so that no fault
may be found with our ministry;

00:36:22.096 --> 00:36:24.298 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“but in every way

00:36:24.298 --> 00:36:28.736 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we recommend ourselves as God’s ministers.”

00:36:42.116 --> 00:36:44.819 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I realized that things like our appearance,

00:36:44.819 --> 00:36:47.755 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
our homes, and our cars

00:36:47.755 --> 00:36:51.659 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—these can all be
a silent witness to Jehovah in themselves.

00:36:51.659 --> 00:36:54.228 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It made sense to me now.

00:36:54.228 --> 00:36:56.530 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s not all about us.

00:36:56.530 --> 00:36:59.000 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I knew what I had to do.

00:37:05.873 --> 00:37:09.777 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Not only did I clean my car,
but later that year,

00:37:09.777 --> 00:37:12.680 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I was able to turn in
my application for pioneering.

00:37:15.116 --> 00:37:19.487 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And I’m glad for the lesson
I learned from my dad.

00:37:19.487 --> 00:37:21.722 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s not all about us.

00:37:23.291 --> 00:37:25.860 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Even in little ways,

00:37:25.860 --> 00:37:29.630 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we can reflect favorably
on the God we love.

00:37:31.198 --> 00:37:35.002 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What made Grayson’s counsel effective?

00:37:36.037 --> 00:37:40.942 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Although he reacted to sitting in the dirty car,

00:37:40.942 --> 00:37:45.012 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he waited until he was calm to give counsel.

00:37:45.012 --> 00:37:49.216 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He based what he said
on God’s standards in the Bible.

00:37:49.216 --> 00:37:53.587 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And it took humility
for his son to see that his cleanliness

00:37:53.587 --> 00:37:58.592 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
could affect how others
view Jehovah’s clean people.

00:37:58.592 --> 00:38:01.262 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Humility helps us to accept correction,

00:38:01.262 --> 00:38:03.731 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but it can do even more.

00:38:03.731 --> 00:38:07.201 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was the topic of this Bethel morning worship,

00:38:07.201 --> 00:38:11.472 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
wherein Brother Mark Noumair asks why humility

00:38:11.472 --> 00:38:16.177 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was such an important lesson for Jesus’ apostles

00:38:16.177 --> 00:38:19.613 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and why it still is for us today.

00:38:20.114 --> 00:38:22.783 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
It is interesting that Peter gives counsel

00:38:22.783 --> 00:38:25.152 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
about cultivating humility.

00:38:25.152 --> 00:38:26.487 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Let’s turn the clock back

00:38:26.487 --> 00:38:28.990 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
and learn why the quality of humility

00:38:28.990 --> 00:38:30.958 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
was indelibly etched

00:38:30.958 --> 00:38:32.827 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
in the mind and heart of Peter.

00:38:32.827 --> 00:38:36.464 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Let’s open our Bibles to Luke chapter 22.

00:38:36.464 --> 00:38:38.499 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In Luke chapter 22,

00:38:38.499 --> 00:38:43.104 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we’ll find Jesus getting ready
for that final Passover in 33 C.E.

00:38:43.104 --> 00:38:46.774 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And in Luke 22, starting in verse 8,

00:38:46.774 --> 00:38:51.779 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
it is Thursday afternoon, Nisan 13,
and what happens?

00:38:51.779 --> 00:38:55.383 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Verse 8: “Jesus sent Peter [there he is]

00:38:55.383 --> 00:38:58.586 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and John, saying: ‘Go and get

00:38:58.586 --> 00:39:01.722 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the Passover ready for us to eat.’”

00:39:01.722 --> 00:39:04.125 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Get it ready, Peter and John.’

00:39:04.125 --> 00:39:08.896 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Verse 9: “They said to him:
‘Where do you want us to get it ready?’”

00:39:08.896 --> 00:39:12.199 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They understood the instructions: Get it ready.

00:39:12.199 --> 00:39:14.201 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jesus said to go into Jerusalem,

00:39:14.201 --> 00:39:17.038 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and you’ll find the man
with the earthenware jar.

00:39:17.038 --> 00:39:20.074 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Verse 12: “And that man

00:39:20.074 --> 00:39:23.177 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“will show you
a large, furnished upper room.

00:39:23.177 --> 00:39:25.880 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Get it ready there.”

00:39:25.880 --> 00:39:30.151 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Verse 13: “So they left 
and found it just as he had told them,

00:39:30.151 --> 00:39:34.688 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and they prepared for the Passover.”

00:39:34.688 --> 00:39:38.793 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Get it ready; prepare the Passover.

00:39:38.793 --> 00:39:41.228 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What would that include?

00:39:41.228 --> 00:39:46.233 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Bread, wine, oil for the lamps,

00:39:46.233 --> 00:39:51.238 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
lamb, a towel, a basin, water.

00:39:51.872 --> 00:39:53.908 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Basin and water

00:39:53.908 --> 00:39:56.744 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—they knew 
how important washing feet was.

00:39:56.744 --> 00:40:00.414 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They witnessed when
Jesus reproved Simon the Pharisee

00:40:00.414 --> 00:40:04.785 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with the statement: Simon,
“you gave me no water for my feet.”

00:40:04.785 --> 00:40:08.022 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Simon, you gave me no water.

00:40:08.022 --> 00:40:10.558 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You missed the mark on this one.’

00:40:10.558 --> 00:40:14.995 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So as they stared
at that basin and water,

00:40:14.995 --> 00:40:18.699 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
as they prepared
and got the room ready,

00:40:18.699 --> 00:40:22.136 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
did they look at each other
and wonder:

00:40:22.136 --> 00:40:24.138 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Who’s going to wash the feet?

00:40:24.138 --> 00:40:25.840 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Who’s going to do it?’

00:40:25.840 --> 00:40:29.677 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They had a golden opportunity
to apply all the things that Jesus

00:40:29.677 --> 00:40:32.780 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
had been teaching them
for three and a half years on humility.

00:40:32.780 --> 00:40:34.782 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This was the time.

00:40:34.782 --> 00:40:37.585 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
After three and a half years,
conduct yourself as a lesser one.

00:40:37.585 --> 00:40:39.386 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Don’t lord it over others.

00:40:39.386 --> 00:40:41.922 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You want to serve others and not be served.

00:40:41.922 --> 00:40:43.991 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This was it; this was the time.

00:40:43.991 --> 00:40:47.628 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They could have showed Jesus
that they got the point; they got it.

00:40:47.628 --> 00:40:50.631 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They had time to think about it
and time to pray about it.

00:40:50.631 --> 00:40:53.534 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was Thursday afternoon,

00:40:53.534 --> 00:40:57.538 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but now we progress
and let’s see what happens.

00:40:57.538 --> 00:41:01.108 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s now progress
to the evening, and it’s Nisan 14.

00:41:01.108 --> 00:41:04.111 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s pick up the account in John chapter 13.

00:41:05.713 --> 00:41:09.383 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They got the room ready,
they followed the instructions,

00:41:09.383 --> 00:41:13.320 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and now let’s go to John 13
and get John’s vantage point from this.

00:41:13.320 --> 00:41:17.358 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He was there;
he was with Peter getting it ready.

00:41:17.358 --> 00:41:22.363 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So now it’s 98 C.E.,
and John is writing this information.

00:41:22.363 --> 00:41:26.400 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He had time to reflect
and to think about this for years,

00:41:26.400 --> 00:41:30.404 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and now look what he says in verse 3:

00:41:30.404 --> 00:41:32.873 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“So Jesus,

00:41:32.873 --> 00:41:37.144 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“knowing that the Father
had given all things into his hands

00:41:37.144 --> 00:41:40.281 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and that he came from God
and was going to God.”

00:41:40.281 --> 00:41:43.851 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Knowing these things
—he understood that.

00:41:43.851 --> 00:41:48.422 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He sat back and said:
‘Jesus knew who he was; he knew all things.

00:41:48.422 --> 00:41:51.525 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘He had the full understanding of his dignity.

00:41:51.525 --> 00:41:54.328 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘He knew that he
had been entrusted with all things.

00:41:54.328 --> 00:41:55.563 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘He knew.

00:41:55.563 --> 00:41:58.566 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘He knew he was the second greatest
personage in the universe.

00:41:58.566 --> 00:42:01.368 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘He knew he was
“the firstborn of all creation.”

00:42:01.368 --> 00:42:04.605 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘He knew he had shared 
with his Father in creating all things.

00:42:04.605 --> 00:42:08.375 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He had knowledge of all this
—knowing all these things.’

00:42:08.375 --> 00:42:11.378 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
John sits back; he writes this.

00:42:11.378 --> 00:42:13.747 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And then knowing this,

00:42:13.747 --> 00:42:17.818 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
verse 4 is the contrast:

00:42:17.818 --> 00:42:22.823 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘He got up from the evening meal
and laid aside his outer garments.

00:42:22.823 --> 00:42:25.859 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Taking a towel,
he wraps it around his waist.

00:42:25.859 --> 00:42:28.195 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘After that, he puts the water
into the basin

00:42:28.195 --> 00:42:30.097 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘and starts to wash
the feet of the disciples

00:42:30.097 --> 00:42:33.100 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and dry them off with the towel
that was wrapped around him.’

00:42:33.100 --> 00:42:35.703 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Knowing who He was,

00:42:35.703 --> 00:42:38.906 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
John said He did this.

00:42:38.906 --> 00:42:43.043 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But not only does John reflect
on who Jesus was,

00:42:43.043 --> 00:42:46.680 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
no, he reflects on why Jesus did it.

00:42:46.680 --> 00:42:47.781 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Why did he do it?

00:42:47.781 --> 00:42:50.117 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s what John was interested in,

00:42:50.117 --> 00:42:54.388 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and we get that answer back in verse 1,

00:42:54.388 --> 00:42:56.523 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
where John says why:

00:42:56.523 --> 00:43:00.594 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Because he loved his own
that were in the world;

00:43:00.594 --> 00:43:03.664 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he loved them to the end.’

00:43:03.664 --> 00:43:06.467 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
John said He “loved them to the end.”

00:43:06.467 --> 00:43:07.868 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What does that mean?

00:43:07.868 --> 00:43:11.772 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He wanted to instill in them qualities
that would help them conquer the world,

00:43:11.772 --> 00:43:15.242 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
qualities that would strengthen
the Christian congregation,

00:43:15.242 --> 00:43:18.412 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
qualities such as unselfish love
and humility.

00:43:18.412 --> 00:43:20.414 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He loved them to the end.

00:43:20.414 --> 00:43:22.416 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He never gave up on them.

00:43:22.416 --> 00:43:26.287 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They had their weaknesses,
but he did not give up.

00:43:26.287 --> 00:43:29.523 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, for Peter, some 30 years later,

00:43:29.523 --> 00:43:31.792 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he’s thinking about humility.

00:43:31.792 --> 00:43:34.161 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
John, some 60 years later,

00:43:34.161 --> 00:43:36.630 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
after the lesson Jesus taught
about humility,

00:43:36.630 --> 00:43:40.467 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
it’s echoing loud and clear
in his mind and heart.

00:43:40.467 --> 00:43:44.805 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
However, the fact remains
that neither of them

00:43:44.805 --> 00:43:48.075 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
had the humility at the time
to apply what Jesus

00:43:48.075 --> 00:43:50.344 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
had been teaching them
for three and a half years.

00:43:51.412 --> 00:43:56.417 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, after John finished his writing, he sat back;

00:43:56.417 --> 00:43:59.286 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he was under inspiration;
he finished that writing.

00:43:59.286 --> 00:44:02.389 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Did he sit back,
reread what he just wrote,

00:44:02.389 --> 00:44:05.059 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and perhaps say to himself:

00:44:05.059 --> 00:44:08.562 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘I wish I could have written

00:44:08.562 --> 00:44:13.567 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘that after Jesus washed the feet
of one or two of his disciples,

00:44:13.567 --> 00:44:17.371 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘I got up and washed the feet

00:44:17.371 --> 00:44:19.540 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘of the rest of my brothers?

00:44:19.540 --> 00:44:24.144 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘I took that towel, and I imitated the Christ?

00:44:24.144 --> 00:44:27.348 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Or, Peter and I got up?’

00:44:27.348 --> 00:44:30.150 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But the point is, they didn’t.

00:44:30.150 --> 00:44:32.186 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What can we learn?

00:44:32.186 --> 00:44:35.923 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Don’t allow valuable lessons
that Jesus teaches us

00:44:35.923 --> 00:44:38.058 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to echo in our minds and hearts

00:44:38.058 --> 00:44:42.996 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
only after we missed
the opportunity to apply them.

00:44:42.996 --> 00:44:47.968 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So in a practical setting
for us serving here at Bethel:

00:44:47.968 --> 00:44:52.106 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Even though I know
I have the seniority

00:44:52.106 --> 00:44:54.908 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘—I have full knowledge of my seniority—

00:44:54.908 --> 00:44:59.913 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘will I get up and fight the attitude
of entitlement?

00:44:59.913 --> 00:45:04.852 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘I know I have
authority entrusted to me as the overseer;

00:45:04.852 --> 00:45:09.022 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘I am the overseer;
I know that. I have full knowledge of that.

00:45:09.022 --> 00:45:11.658 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Fine, will I get up

00:45:11.658 --> 00:45:14.294 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘and roll my sleeves back
and do the grunt work?

00:45:14.294 --> 00:45:17.798 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Or do I just find pleasure
in giving orders?

00:45:17.798 --> 00:45:21.101 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘I know I have
a wonderful privilege of service;

00:45:21.101 --> 00:45:23.804 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘I know that; others know it too.

00:45:23.804 --> 00:45:27.975 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Fine, but will I get up to train others?’

00:45:27.975 --> 00:45:32.346 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Jackson reminded us of this
at the last Gilead graduation

00:45:32.346 --> 00:45:36.717 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when he said to treasure your privileges,
but don’t hoard them.

00:45:36.717 --> 00:45:38.752 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That means we have to get up.

00:45:38.752 --> 00:45:43.624 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It takes humility 
to train others to take our place.

00:45:43.624 --> 00:45:46.527 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘As a brother or a sister,

00:45:46.527 --> 00:45:51.398 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘I know I have more experience
than the other person in my job.

00:45:51.398 --> 00:45:54.668 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘I know I have the experience; I know that.

00:45:54.668 --> 00:45:57.271 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘I have more experience than my workmate.

00:45:57.271 --> 00:46:02.276 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Fine, but will I get up in all humility

00:46:02.276 --> 00:46:05.145 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘and share information that I have

00:46:05.145 --> 00:46:08.382 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘with others to make their job easier?

00:46:08.382 --> 00:46:12.386 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Or will I hold the knowledge I have hostage?’

00:46:12.386 --> 00:46:16.657 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If we get up in all humility
and do these things,

00:46:16.657 --> 00:46:21.662 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
then we can say that Jesus’ humble act,
as recorded here in John 13,

00:46:21.662 --> 00:46:24.598 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
has made a lasting
and indelible impression

00:46:24.598 --> 00:46:27.734 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
not only on Peter and John
but on me.

00:46:28.735 --> 00:46:31.572 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What a powerful lesson!

00:46:31.572 --> 00:46:34.575 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Humility will improve the way

00:46:34.575 --> 00:46:38.111 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we carry out our theocratic assignments.

00:46:38.111 --> 00:46:43.116 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It honors our fellow workers,
and it promotes unity.

00:46:43.116 --> 00:46:47.087 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Unified servants of God get things done.

00:46:47.087 --> 00:46:49.089 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In Peru,

00:46:49.089 --> 00:46:53.427 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
local brothers worked 
with international servants and volunteers

00:46:53.427 --> 00:46:56.730 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to complete two new Assembly Halls.

00:46:56.730 --> 00:46:58.732 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In this report,

00:46:58.732 --> 00:47:02.002 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
hear what the brothers
learned from working together

00:47:02.002 --> 00:47:04.271 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and how the new Assembly Halls

00:47:04.271 --> 00:47:07.441 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
are being used to glorify Jehovah.

00:47:27.127 --> 00:47:29.196 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
I suppose whatever we give to Jehovah

00:47:29.196 --> 00:47:32.332 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
is little in comparison with what he gives to us.

00:47:32.332 --> 00:47:34.401 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
And like Malachi 3:10 says, you know,

00:47:34.401 --> 00:47:36.036 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
we just have to ‘bring in the tenth part.’

00:47:36.036 --> 00:47:38.038 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s really all that Jehovah is asking,

00:47:38.038 --> 00:47:40.040 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but he pours out a blessing.

00:47:40.040 --> 00:47:43.477 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And part of those blessings from Malachi 3:10,

00:47:43.477 --> 00:47:46.914 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I consider to be
the friendships that we’ve gained.

00:47:47.247 --> 00:47:49.249 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
For me, my favorite thing is the people.

00:47:49.249 --> 00:47:52.386 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
It’s always just getting to work

00:47:52.386 --> 00:47:54.388 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
with your brothers every day.

00:47:54.388 --> 00:47:58.225 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The personalities shine through,
even with language differences.

00:47:58.225 --> 00:48:00.928 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You just make friends,
and you just get this taste

00:48:00.928 --> 00:48:03.230 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of what the new world is going to be like.

00:48:03.230 --> 00:48:05.499 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Side by side with our brothers,

00:48:05.499 --> 00:48:08.936 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we’ve made parent figures
and brother and sister figures,

00:48:08.936 --> 00:48:12.739 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and everybody just becomes
part of such a solid family.

00:48:14.341 --> 00:48:17.578 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Working along with the local brothers and sisters

00:48:17.578 --> 00:48:19.079 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
made it clear to me

00:48:19.079 --> 00:48:21.448 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
that we really are in the organization

00:48:21.448 --> 00:48:24.885 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that Jehovah is directing today.

00:48:26.720 --> 00:48:29.723 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
What I have seen is how Jehovah’s spirit

00:48:29.723 --> 00:48:32.359 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
operates in his organization.

00:48:32.593 --> 00:48:35.662 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There were many international servants here

00:48:35.662 --> 00:48:37.698 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from various countries,

00:48:37.698 --> 00:48:40.100 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with different personalities,

00:48:40.100 --> 00:48:43.136 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
along with our local brothers
with their distinct customs.

00:48:44.371 --> 00:48:47.808 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But when it was time to work, we were as one.

00:48:48.976 --> 00:48:52.312 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There wasn’t a big guy, a little guy,

00:48:52.312 --> 00:48:54.881 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
someone more intelligent, or less intelligent.

00:48:54.881 --> 00:48:57.884 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We all formed one united team.

00:48:58.819 --> 00:49:01.321 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The language definitely was an issue for me.

00:49:02.623 --> 00:49:04.625 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At first I thought,

00:49:04.625 --> 00:49:07.828 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Will I really be able to work with the brothers?’

00:49:07.828 --> 00:49:10.597 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Since I didn’t understand the language,

00:49:10.597 --> 00:49:13.033 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
how could I explain
the work that had to be done?

00:49:17.104 --> 00:49:19.640 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Really, if you go in there with a good attitude

00:49:19.640 --> 00:49:21.908 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and you’re just having
a good time working with your brothers,

00:49:21.908 --> 00:49:23.777 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
you’re not going to have too much of a problem.

00:49:23.777 --> 00:49:25.979 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Smiles
—they cross borders.

00:49:33.654 --> 00:49:35.656 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
The Chiclayo dedication program

00:49:35.656 --> 00:49:38.725 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
was held April 9, 2016,

00:49:38.725 --> 00:49:40.761 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
and the Trujillo Assembly Hall

00:49:40.761 --> 00:49:43.163 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
was dedicated shortly thereafter,

00:49:43.163 --> 00:49:45.599 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
on July 31.

00:49:50.137 --> 00:49:53.040 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All present marveled with appreciation

00:49:53.040 --> 00:49:55.642 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at seeing the facilities,

00:49:55.642 --> 00:49:57.678 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
their own new Assembly Hall.

00:50:01.682 --> 00:50:03.684 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Before, we had to work a lot,

00:50:03.684 --> 00:50:06.153 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
maybe up to 15 days beforehand

00:50:06.153 --> 00:50:09.056 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
to prepare a completely inappropriate site.

00:50:09.056 --> 00:50:10.490 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Not anymore.

00:50:10.490 --> 00:50:12.693 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now the brothers only need to maintain it

00:50:12.693 --> 00:50:16.263 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and simply arrive
in order to enjoy their assembly.

00:50:17.297 --> 00:50:19.366 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
I’m sure that this new Assembly Hall

00:50:19.366 --> 00:50:21.134 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
will strengthen the spirituality

00:50:21.134 --> 00:50:23.036 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
of our dear brothers and sisters.

00:50:24.638 --> 00:50:27.874 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If I can say something about the video monitors:

00:50:27.874 --> 00:50:31.545 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They’ve revolutionized
Jehovah’s method of teaching.

00:50:32.813 --> 00:50:34.915 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
We get so much more out of the talks now

00:50:34.915 --> 00:50:35.982 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
because we can see

00:50:35.982 --> 00:50:37.551 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
the gestures of the brothers.

00:50:37.551 --> 00:50:39.553 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
It really touches the heart.

00:50:39.553 --> 00:50:41.722 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s so amazing!

00:50:42.856 --> 00:50:45.692 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I remember more than 25 years ago,

00:50:45.692 --> 00:50:47.894 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I prayed to Jehovah and said,

00:50:47.894 --> 00:50:51.865 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Jehovah, please,
permit me at some point to see

00:50:51.865 --> 00:50:53.867 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
an Assembly Hall here.”

00:50:53.867 --> 00:50:55.869 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And now Jehovah let me

00:50:55.869 --> 00:50:57.871 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
be part of the buying process,

00:50:57.871 --> 00:51:00.006 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of getting the documentation,

00:51:00.006 --> 00:51:02.209 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and of being part of the construction.

00:51:02.209 --> 00:51:04.611 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And I remember, and I say,

00:51:04.611 --> 00:51:07.047 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Jehovah answered my prayer.”

00:51:09.282 --> 00:51:12.953 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Well, it affected me

00:51:12.953 --> 00:51:15.555 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
seeing the construction progress

00:51:15.555 --> 00:51:17.557 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
because when we first arrived

00:51:17.557 --> 00:51:19.726 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
at our project in Chiclayo,

00:51:19.726 --> 00:51:21.728 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
you know what the brothers had

00:51:21.728 --> 00:51:24.698 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
and what they were using as an Assembly Hall.

00:51:24.698 --> 00:51:26.700 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
And then to see the finished project

00:51:26.700 --> 00:51:28.969 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
that we see now,

00:51:28.969 --> 00:51:31.905 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
I’m so happy for the brothers and sisters.

00:51:31.905 --> 00:51:34.775 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
It’s so beautiful, clean, neat, and tidy.

00:51:34.775 --> 00:51:37.544 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
It’s like, in reality, for where it is,

00:51:37.544 --> 00:51:39.579 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
it’s a little jewel within that whole city

00:51:39.579 --> 00:51:43.750 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
to me when I see the completed project.

00:51:43.750 --> 00:51:48.755 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And I know that brothers
do just love to be able to care for that place,

00:51:48.755 --> 00:51:52.759 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to be able to worship Jehovah there,
and to be with their brothers and sisters.

00:51:52.759 --> 00:51:55.462 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There’s nothing that will ever compare

00:51:55.462 --> 00:51:58.765 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with this wonderful experience
we’ve been able to have.

00:51:59.800 --> 00:52:03.270 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s been great!

00:52:08.208 --> 00:52:10.877 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We’ve enjoyed a wonderful program.

00:52:10.877 --> 00:52:13.780 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our videos showed us so many of the ways

00:52:13.780 --> 00:52:17.150 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we can present our gift to Jehovah.

00:52:17.150 --> 00:52:19.152 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I agree.

00:52:19.152 --> 00:52:21.888 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We saw our brothers, young and old,

00:52:21.888 --> 00:52:24.357 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
give their best in the ministry,

00:52:24.357 --> 00:52:27.761 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the congregation, at Bethel,

00:52:27.761 --> 00:52:29.996 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and on construction projects.

00:52:29.996 --> 00:52:33.133 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And we heard good counsel to be humble,

00:52:33.133 --> 00:52:37.003 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
morally clean, and physically clean.

00:52:37.003 --> 00:52:39.306 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And to conclude our program,

00:52:39.306 --> 00:52:43.076 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we have greetings
from our brothers and sisters in Chad.

00:52:44.144 --> 00:52:47.714 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Chad is located in north-central Africa.

00:52:47.714 --> 00:52:50.317 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
With the Sahara Desert in the north,

00:52:50.317 --> 00:52:54.154 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
most of Chad’s more than 13 million people

00:52:54.154 --> 00:52:57.157 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
live in the fertile southern regions.

00:52:57.157 --> 00:53:00.193 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Fewer than a thousand brothers live and preach

00:53:00.193 --> 00:53:04.397 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in this vast field dotted with remote villages.

00:53:04.397 --> 00:53:07.567 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The capital city is N’Djamena.

00:53:07.567 --> 00:53:10.503 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Five congregations
are busy spreading the good news

00:53:10.503 --> 00:53:13.673 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the city and its surrounding area.

00:53:13.673 --> 00:53:18.712 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
One of these, just south of the capital,
is the Walia Congregation.

00:53:19.512 --> 00:53:22.716 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They preach regularly along the Logone River,

00:53:22.716 --> 00:53:26.853 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
where they often meet people
traveling from faraway areas.

00:53:27.687 --> 00:53:30.690 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Their busy activity also helped to establish

00:53:30.690 --> 00:53:33.760 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a new congregation in nearby Koundoul.

00:53:33.760 --> 00:53:36.730 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The brothers in Koundoul and Walia

00:53:36.730 --> 00:53:41.201 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
send us
their heartfelt Christian love and greetings.

00:53:41.201 --> 00:53:43.370 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We pray for Jehovah to bless

00:53:43.370 --> 00:53:47.407 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
their gifts of brotherly affection and self-sacrifice.

00:53:47.407 --> 00:53:49.943 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Thank you for joining us.

00:53:49.943 --> 00:53:53.380 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

00:53:53.380 --> 00:53:56.216 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
this is JW Broadcasting.

